President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation recognizing Human Rights Day, Bill of Rights Day, and Human Rights Week. In the proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of the Bill of Rights in protecting individual liberties and limiting government power. The Bill of Rights has been a model for other countries in developing their own safeguards for human rights. Trump reaffirms his commitment to defending the Bill of Rights and upholding the Constitution, and expresses a desire for the rule of law and liberty to triumph over oppression worldwide. He calls upon the people of the United States to mark these observances with appropriate ceremonies and activities.